\section{Function Layout}

\subsection{General Principles}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Avoid nested functions (use separate functions instead).
    \item Avoid use of global variables (use function parameters or constants).
    \item All variables should be initiated at the beginning of a function when possible.
    \item Do not reassign variable names that are passed into a function.
    \item Do not change variable names after initiation.
    \item All functions start with a docstring (see comment sections for example).
    \item When inputting/outputting multiple values, consider using NamedTuples for clarity.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Function Example}

\begin{lstlisting}
"""
    calculate_distance_fnc(point1_M::Vector{Float64}, 
                           point2_M::Vector{Float64}) -> Float64

Calculates the Euclidean distance between two points.

# Arguments
- `point1_M::Vector{Float64}`: First point coordinates in meters (3x1)
- `point2_M::Vector{Float64}`: Second point coordinates in meters (3x1)

# Returns
- `Float64`: Distance between points in meters

# Examples
```julia
p1_M = [0.0, 0.0, 0.0]
p2_M = [3.0, 4.0, 0.0]
distance_M = calculate_distance_fnc(p1_M, p2_M)  # Returns 5.0
```
"""
function calculate_distance_fnc(point1_M::Vector{Float64}, 
                                point2_M::Vector{Float64})
    # Calculate difference vector
    delta_M = point2_M - point1_M
    
    # Calculate Euclidean distance
    distance_M = sqrt(sum(delta_M.^2))
    
    return distance_M
end
\end{lstlisting}
