\subsection{Julia-Specific Notes}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Functions automatically return the last expression (explicit \texttt{return} is optional but recommended for clarity).
    \item Use \texttt{::Type} annotations for function arguments in public APIs.
    \item Multiple return values use tuples or NamedTuples: \texttt{return (value1, value2)} or \texttt{return (name1=value1, name2=value2)}
    \item Use \texttt{!} suffix for functions that modify their arguments (e.g., \texttt{sort!()})
\end{itemize}

