\section{Variable Naming Conventions}

\subsection{General Rules}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Name variables using \texttt{snake\_case}.
    \item Append units/type suffix to variable name in UPPERCASE.
    \item Function names should end in \texttt{\_fnc}.
    \item Type/Struct names should use \texttt{CamelCase}.
    \item Constants use lowercase with \texttt{k} prefix and UPPERCASE suffix (kCONSTANT).
    \item Avoid vectors/arrays containing multiple units or types.
    \item Use descriptive naming for variables.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Suffix Convention}

\noindent\textbf{IMPORTANT:} ALL variables must have a suffix indicating their type/unit.

